üß© What is a LinkedList?
A LinkedList is a linear data structure in which elements are stored in nodes where one node knows the address of another nodes and
they are linked through this address where,
Each node contains:
     a. Data ‚Üí (can be a variable, object, or even a custom class)
     b. Address (Reference) ‚Üí pointing to the next node in the list.
Note:- Unlike arrays, linked lists do not store elements in continuous memory locations ‚Äî they are linked through references (addresses).

üß† Structure of a Node ?
A Node is the basic building block of a LinkedList.
class Node<T> {
    T data;         // stores data
    Node next;     // stores reference to next node
}

ü™Ñ Important Terminology ?
| Term     | Meaning                                             |
| -------- | --------------------------------------------------- |
| **Head** | First node of the linked list                       |
| **Tail** | Last node of the linked list (its `next` is `null`) |
| **Node** | A structure that holds data + next node address     |
| **Null** | Indicates the end of the list                       |

üéµ Real-world Examples ?
     - Music Player ‚Üí You can move one song forward or backward.
     - Web Browser History ‚Üí You can move to the previous or next page.

üåø Types of LinkedList ?
1Ô∏è‚É£ Singly LinkedList :
           - Each node points only to the next node.
           - Traversal: Forward direction only.
Ex - Head ‚Üí [Data|Next] ‚Üí [Data|Next] ‚Üí null
           - Singly LinkedList can be:
                    singly linkedlist 
                      /         \
                     /           \
                 circuler      non-circuler
                          - Non-Circular ‚Üí last node points to null
                          - Circular ‚Üí last node points back to head

2Ô∏è‚É£ Doubly LinkedList
           - Each node points to both previous and next nodes.
           - Traversal: Forward and backward.
Ex - null ‚Üê [Prev|Data|Next] ‚Üî [Prev|Data|Next] ‚Üî null
           - Doubly LinkedList can also be:
                 doubly linkedlist 
                      /         \
                     /           \
                 circuler      non-circuler
                          - Non-Circular ‚Üí ends with null
                          - Circular ‚Üí last node connects back to head

